 moderate dose, to stop involuntarily grinding my teeth and telling everyone they were my best friend. After that, I felt like myself or, maybe I felt unlike myself because I no longer felt depressed. I could look outside on a gloomy afternoon and think, the sky is gray, instead of, what is the point of ever going outside?On bupropion, food didnt hold the appeal it had once held. It became a bit of a chore, chewing food. For the first time in my life, I would forget to have lunch, leave burritos half uneaten, find myself unable to finish dessert. It should be reflexive to eat when were hungry, to stop when were satisfied but this was the first time I could remember my brain receiving those messages. A genie had granted the wish that I had been making since I was a teenager: Release me from my food fixation.Two years ago, delivered me from . Now Id like to find a cleaner escape, one as effective as , as compelling to me as self-deprivation. Or Id like to learn to live without trying to escape. Or maybe Id like to refocus my lens, to stop seeing my brain, my body, as a prison.Check your Report Free (http://portal.info-nation.eu/nvx/vzjq79sftrrc/ZsZf6fTd48Fi4TlTDfRf6RTr8TtCiGCT1rQ84XtCSjTSTrQ4TimSGT3SKTir8iK8ETi4uuX48o1iejQ84drQziCQ4juuuuVPZf6R6fsRPfuufwsDuuiC2d8r)						&nbsp;			 (http://portal.info-nation.eu/nvx/vzjq79sftrrc/ZsZf6fTd48Fi4TlTDfRf6RTr8TtCiGCT1rQ84XtCSjTSTrQ4TimSGT3SKTir8iK8ETi4uuX48o1iejQ84drQziCQ4juuuuVPZf6R6fsRPfuufwsDuuiC2d8r)																																																																																				ceaseHere (http://portal.info-nation.eu/u/jqco78qvy/ZsZf6fTd48Fi4TlTDfRf6RTr8TtCiGCT1rQ84XtCSjTSTrQ4TimSGT3SKTir8iK8ETi4uuX48o1iejQ84drQziCQ4juuuuVPZf6R6fsRPfuufwsDuuiC2d8r)			23638 W.Lyons Avenue468Newhall,CA 91321						In the fall of 2014 the author decided to quit the prescription medications she has been taking to treat her , and insomnia, and began the process of gradually reducing her dosages. In Going Off, a series of posts in the coming w